/**
 DataReceiver.m (sdkdemo)

 PURPOSE:  Central router for BLE packets from the R7 ring and session manager for "Night" streaming.

 This class handles:
  1) BLE RX routing (motion / HR / SpO2)
  2) Session state (start/stop, reconnect behavior)
  3) Command scheduling for overnight streaming (vitals + motion loop)
  4) Export (motion CSV + vitals JSON) + lightweight UI notifications
  5) Watchdogs for long-running reliability (motion stalls, vitals stalls, dead-air stalls)

 HIGH-LEVEL NIGHT FLOW
 
 User presses Start Night -> startNightSession:
   - Creates sessionId, writes session_start marker
   - Enables realtimeCaptureEnabled (allows vitals packets to be processed)
   - Sends HR_CONTROL ON (some firmwares only emit HR packets when this is enabled)
   - Kicks off syncData (device time/user info/etc.)
   - Starts:
       a) Night loop scheduler (SpO2 -> Motion -> HR -> repeat)
       b) Motion watchdog (restart motion if no packets during motion phase)
       c) Vitals watchdog (re-send ON commands if no vitals packets during vitals phases)
       d) Session liveness watchdog (soft reset if no packets at all for N minutes)

 NIGHT LOOP TIMING
   SpO2 phase:   kNightSpO2Seconds  (HR + O2 commands are ON)
   Motion phase: kNightMotionSeconds (motion command ON)
   HR phase:     kNightHRSeconds    (HR + O2 commands are ON)
 
 NOTE: SpO2 + HR phases are intentionally treated the same to maximize samples.
        (SpO2 often won’t parse/emit without HR enabled on some firmwares.)

 STOP BEHAVIOR
 stopNightSession:
   - Writes session_end marker
   - Stops the loop + watchdogs
   - Force-stops HR/O2 streaming (forceStopVitalsNow)
   - Turns HR_CONTROL OFF
   - Flushes motion buffer + exports vitals JSONs

 EXPORT FILES (Documents/)
   motion_<sessionId>.csv
   combined_<sessionId>.txt
   vitals_<sessionId>.json

 */

